sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: vgb promoter comes from Vitreoscilla sp. and fdhF comes from E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device expresses RFP,YFP,CFP respectively under different oxygen concentration. RFP is expressed under anaerobic conditions. YFP is expressed under microaerobic conditions. CFP is expressed under aerobic conditions and is repressed with the existence of TetR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We construct tetR to resist CFP expression under microaerobic and anaerobic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MA Keyue

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: vgb promoter comes from Vitreoscilla sp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The expression of YFP and tetR is under the control of microaerobic promoter vgb. The expression of tetR will repress Ptet.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because vgb promoter induces high expression under microaerobic conditions and induces lower expression under anaerobic conditions, we used medium RBS to resist it from inducing expression under anaerobic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: HUA Yijie, PI Ruoxi, XIA Yu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The expression of RFP and tetR is under the control of anaerobic promoter fdhF. The expression of tetR will repress Ptet.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: XU Chenlin, PI Ruoxi, HUA Yijie, MA Lie

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13602
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Tet operator with CFP reporter (with LVA tag) [R/Tc+]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Christopher Batten, Victoria Chou, Kenneth Nesmith

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ECFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: enhanced cyan fluorescent protein derived from A. victoria GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Cyan fluorescent protein (ECFP) reporter coding sequence without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_E0022 cyan fluorescent protein is based on BioBrick part BBa_E0021. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ecfp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part accepts POPS to generate EYFP under the medium strength RBS B0032.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Tabor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: vgb promoter comes from Vitreoscilla sp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: vgb promoter is induced under microaerobic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We construct this promoter, according to the reference: "Construction of highly efficient E. coli expression systems containing low oxygen induced promoter and partition region" by Liu Tao et al.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: HUA Yijie, MA Keyue, XIA Yu

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K387003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PfdhF: fdhF promoter, a hypoxia inducible promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yupeng He

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RBS-RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RFP, BBa_E1010, with Elowitz RBS, BBa_B0034.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part was needed for downstream applications. There can be no expression of a reporter without a ribosome binding site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kathy Lam, Danielle Nash

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

Lutz R, Bujard H., Independent and tight regulation of transcriptional units in Escherichia coli via the LacR/O, the TetR/O and AraC/I1-I2 regulatory elements. Nucleic Acids Res. 1997 Mar 15;25(6):1203-10. PMID: 9092630

References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

Lutz R, Bujard H., Independent and tight regulation of transcriptional units in Escherichia coli via the LacR/O, the TetR/O and AraC/I1-I2 regulatory elements. Nucleic Acids Res. 1997 Mar 15;25(6):1203-10. PMID: 9092630

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL

Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
